==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Instrumentally
<hw>In`stru*men"tal*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>By means of an instrument or agency; as means to an end.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They will argue that the end being essentially beneficial, the
means become <qex>instrumentally</qex> so.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With instruments of music; <as>as, a song
<ex>instrumentally</ex> accompanied</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Mason.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instrumentalness</ent>⟦br⟧
